b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe29195.htm)  [Next](sbe29197.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1421228750/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n_The Grihya Sutras, Part 1 (SBE29)_ , by Hermann Oldenberg, [1886], at sacred-\ntexts.com\n\n* * *\n\n### KA _N_ _D_ IK\xc3\x82 6.\n\n1\\. Now the cure for headache.\n\n2\\. Having moistened his hands, he passes them over his eye-brows with (the\nverse), 'From the eyes, from the ears, from the whiskers, from the chin, from\nthe forehead, I drive away this disease of the head.'\n\n3\\. If (only) one side (of the head aches, he recites the verse), 'Cleaver!\nThou with the disfigured eyes! White-wing! Renowned one! And thou with the\nvarious-coloured wing! Let his head not ache.'\n\n4\\. Then it will get better.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: III, 7](sbe29197.htm)\n\n"